4.3 In the event of any dispute or controversy arising between you and us under the Agreement, both parties shall first attempt to resolve it through amicable negotiations. Should negotiations fail, you agree to submit the dispute or controversy to the judicial authorities in the country/region where the service operator is located.
4.4 If you encounter any issues during the account deactivation process that you cannot resolve or have any questions during the process, you may contact customer service for assistance.
6.6 Obtaining Copies of Personal Information
If you have the need to inquire, copy, correct, supplement, delete your personal information in the game, or obtain a copy of your personal information, you can contact [homelandhk@icloud.com] to do so.
6.7 Responding to your request for rights
Please understand and agree that you may be required to provide a written request or otherwise prove your identity for security purposes. We may ask you to verify your identity before processing your request.
In principle, we do not charge you for reasonable requests, but for requests that are repeated more than reasonably possible, we will charge a fee of a certain cost, depending on the circumstances. We may refuse requests that require excessive technical means, high costs, or other significant difficulties (for example, the need to develop new systems or fundamentally change existing practices), or that pose a risk to the legal rights and interests of others. After verifying your identity, we will respond to you or provide you with an explanation within the time period required by local laws and regulations, regardless of whether your request will be fulfilled.
We will not be able to respond to your request in the following cases:
(1) Related to our fulfillment of obligations under laws and regulations.
(2) Directly related to national security and national defense security.
(3) Directly related to public safety, public health, and major public interests.
(4) Directly related to criminal investigation, prosecution, trial and execution of judgment, etc.
(5) We have sufficient evidence that you have subjective malicious intent or abuse your rights.
(6) For the purpose of safeguarding the life, property, and other important legal rights and interests of you or other individuals, but it is difficult to obtain your consent.
(7) Responding to your request will seriously harm the legal rights and interests of the subject of personal information or other individuals and organizations.
(8) Where trade secrets are involved.
7. Cookies and Similar Technologies
We want you to learn about our use of these technologies, so this section explains the types of technologies we use, what they are used for, and your choices regarding their use.
(1) What are Cookies and Advertising Identifiers?
Cookies are small data files that are usually stored on your device as you browse and use websites and online services. They are widely used to make websites work more efficiently and to provide report information and assistance services.
(2) Why do we use cookies and advertising identifiers?
The use of Cookies allows us to provide you with a more convenient service while you are online.
(3) How do I select cookies and advertising identifiers?
When using the customer service function before logging in, a random string is generated to identify an anonymous user, so that the anonymous user can get the previous chat history when he/she uses the customer service next time.
8. Changes
We may revise this policy from time to time. When the terms of this policy are changed, we will notify you of the changed guidelines in an appropriate manner when the version is updated. Please read the changed privacy protection policy or the content of the policy carefully. Your continued use of Fishing Frenzy: Sea World indicates your consent to our collection, processing, or use of your personal information in accordance with the updated privacy protection policy.
9. Protection of Minors
We attach great importance to the protection of minors' personal information and continue to explore ways to update the protection of minors' personal information. In order to better protect the physical and mental health of minors, we recommend that minor users should read and agree to this policy under the supervision of their parents or other guardians before using the game.
10. Contact Us
When you have other complaints, suggestions, or questions related to minors' personal information, please contact us through the game's customer service. You can also send your question to [homelandhk@icloud.com]. We will review the issue as soon as possible and respond within fifteen days after verifying your user identity.
